# Markdoc Syntax Reference

Markdoc is a powerful, extensible syntax for writing content that compiles to HTML using a schema-based approach.

## Frontmatter

Use frontmatter to define metadata at the top of your file.

```yaml
---
title: Getting Started
description: Learn the basics of Markdoc.
---
```

## Headings

Headings are written using Markdown-style `#` syntax.

```markdown
# Heading 1
## Heading 2
### Heading 3
```

{% callout type="info" %}
Headings can be referenced automatically when rendering a table of contents.
{% /callout %}

## Variables

Variables can be used for templating dynamic content.

```markdown
Hello {{ name %}!
```

Pass variables through your rendering context in JavaScript.

```js
markdoc.transform(ast, { variables: { name: "Shelton" } });
```

## Tags

Tags allow structured components within documents.

```markdown
{% callout type="warning" %}
Handle with care.
{% /callout %}
```

| Tag | Description |
| --- | --- |
| `{% callout %}` | Creates styled alert boxes. |
| `{% code %}` | Renders formatted code examples. |
| `{% include %}` | Includes external Markdoc files. |



## Foo

## Expressions

Markdoc supports conditional logic and iteration.

```markdown
{% if user %}
Welcome back, {{ user.name %}!
{% else %}
Please log in.
{% /if %}
```

{% code lang="js" %}
if (user) console.log("Welcome back!");
{% /code %}

